margin-top: 10px;\">üß™ Using the Wrong Renderer‚Äôs <code style=\"font-size: 13px; background: #ececec; padding: 2px 5px; color: #5b5b5b; text-shadow: 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, .5); border-radius: 4px; font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Inconsolata', 'Fira Mono', 'Droid Sans Mono', 'Source Code Pro', monospace;\">act()</code> Should Warn</h2>\n<p style=\"margin: 0;\">The <code style=\"font-size: 13px; background: #ececec; padding: 2px 5px; color: #5b5b5b; text-shadow: 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, .5); border-radius: 4px; font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Inconsolata', 'Fira Mono', 'Droid Sans Mono', 'Source Code Pro', monospace;\">act()</code> test helper now properly warns when the helper is important from the wrong renderer.</p>\n\n          <table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:100%; min-width:100%; margin-top: 10px;\" width=\"100%\">\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td height=\"30px\" valign=\"middle\" style=\"line-height:1.3;\">\n              <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/15756\" style=\"color: #c45000; text-decoration: underline;\">https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/15756</a>\n            </td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n      </div>\n    \n              </td>\n            </tr>\n          \n      </table>\n    \n      </div>\n    \n          <!--[if mso | IE]>\n            </td>\n          \n        </tr>\n      \n                  </table>\n                <![endif]-->\n              </td>\n            </tr>\n          </tbody>\n        </table>\n        \n      </div>\n    \n      \n      <!--[if mso | IE]>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n      </table>\n      \n      <table\n         align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"\" style=\"width:600px;\" width=\"600\"\n      >\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"line-height:0px;font-size:0px;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;\">\n      <![endif]-->\n    \n      \n     